Headlines.Author: Jon Kamp

PARAGRAPH.#text: Managers of the Legg Mason ClearBridge Mid Cap Core Fund (SBMAX) hope investors are once again valuing mid-sized companies based on business fundamentals. Getting back to basics plays into the strategy of the $624.8 million fund, where co-managers Brian Angerame and Derek Deutsch hunt for companies that fly under the radar and have under-appreciated strength on their balance sheet, plus strong track records for putting money to work carefully. "Those characteristics fell out of favor when the market rallied" starting last year, and "the market wasn't appreciating cash flows and balance sheets," Angerame said, which made it hard for the fund to distinguish itself.

Headlines.Author: Marietta Cauchi
Headlines.Headline: Summit Partners Buys Majority Stake In Belgium's Ogone

PARAGRAPH.#text: (Adds background.) LONDON (Dow Jones)--Boston-based private equity firm Summit Partners Monday said it has bought a majority stake in Belgium's Ogone, the latest deal involving an online payment processor. Financial details of the transaction weren't disclosed. Ogone has a network of some 150 bank connections and provides online payment services to some 20,000 merchants across Europe with offices in Belgium, the Netherlands, France, Germany, Switzerland, Austria and the U.K. Summit Partners is joining forces with the company's founders and chief executive and its capital will be used to fuel further expansion.
